From the foregoing detailed account, it will be seen that the quires, with the lost quire and those composed of loose leaves omitted, were begun in the following chronological order: 1, 4, 9, 12, 10, 2, 8, 6 (probably), 7, 3, 11, 14, 15,16,18. These, with the exception of 18, which belongs to 1447, cover a period from 10 Deo, 1437, to 27 March, 1441. 2, 6, 7 and 18 each refer to a single visitation of one house. 11 belongs entirely to the Lincoln visitation of 1440, 14 and 15 belong to the Leicester visitation of 1440-1.
